01:42:36,340 --> 01:42:41,110
我只知道每多杀一个人 我就离开我的家越远
I just know that with every man I kill, the farther away from home I feel.

985
01:44:05,890 --> 01:44:10,830
昔日的回忆涌现
by memories of days gone by

986
01:44:12,730 --> 01:44:17,600
孤独中你嘲弄我
In my solitude you taunt me

987
01:44:17,810 --> 01:44:22,570
勾起不死的记忆
with memories that never die

988
01:44:22,780 --> 01:44:27,610
我坐在椅上  满怀绝望
I sit in my chair filled with despair

989
01:44:27,820 --> 01:44:32,780
比任何人都要哀伤
There's no one could be so sad

990
01:44:33,020 --> 01:44:37,420
看着坐着的地方 尽是阴霾
With gloom everywhere I sit and I stare

991
01:44:37,630 --> 01:44:42,120
我很快就会疯掉
I know that I'll soon go mad

992
01:44:51,340 --> 01:44:53,430
有坦克  躲好
Half-track! Cover!

993
01:45:09,190 --> 01:45:13,090
是谁开枪?
Who's doing the shooting? Who's doing the shooting?

994
01:45:33,580 --> 01:45:36,020
准备行动  攻击左边
Get ready to move. Take their left flank!

995
01:45:36,250 --> 01:45:38,450
慢着  提防有诈
Hold on and make sure they're down.

996
01:45:59,970 --> 01:46:03,100
我们是101师  要出来了
101st! We're coming out!

997
01:46:10,080 --> 01:46:13,020
装甲兵第二师
That was a recon. element, 2nd SS.

998
01:46:14,420 --> 01:46:17,880
我们正在等待情报 一定是他们了
We've been expecting a probe. That must have been it.

999
01:46:19,790 --> 01:46:23,090
第二突击队C连米勒上尉
Captain Miller, Charlie Company, 2nd Rangers.

1000
01:46:23,300 --> 01:46:25,390
501师E连汉德森下士
Corporal Henderson, Easy Company, 501st.

1001
01:46:25,600 --> 01:46:29,430
506团第一队瑞恩 506团第三队托恩比
Ryan, First of 506th. Toynbee, Third of 506th.

1002
01:46:29,640 --> 01:46:35,370
詹姆斯法兰西斯瑞恩? 对  你怎么会知道?
-James Francis Ryan?  -Yes,sir.How did you guess that?

1003
01:46:46,150 --> 01:46:52,490
看来敌方攻势猛烈 对  是小组部队的进攻
-Looks like you got hit pretty hard.  -Yes,sir.Small unit action.

1004
01:46:54,860 --> 01:46:59,230
他们的88公厘炮威力强劲
They came in and beat the hell out of us with 88s.

1005
01:47:04,740 --> 01:47:08,140
要是你们就是救兵 我可要投诉
Tell you what. If you're our relief, I'm going to file a complaint.

1006
01:47:08,380 --> 01:47:10,810
我不会怪你
I wouldn't blame you.

1007
01:47:11,050 --> 01:47:14,240
谁是你的指挥官?
Who's your CO?

1008
01:47:14,450 --> 01:47:17,080
原本是简宁斯上尉
It would've been Captain Jennings.

1009
01:47:17,290 --> 01:47:20,410
但现在唯有以下士充当指挥
I'm afraid the best we can muster up now is a corporal.

1010
01:47:21,860 --> 01:47:24,830
那你们为何来这里?
So what are you guys all about?

1011
01:47:25,060 --> 01:47:28,550
我们为他而来  瑞恩
We're here for him. Ryan.

1012
01:47:28,800 --> 01:47:30,630
我?
Me, sir?

1013
01:47:39,570 --> 01:47:42,810
你是爱阿华州的 詹姆斯法兰西斯瑞恩吧?
James Francis Ryan of lowa?

1014
01:47:43,010 --> 01:47:48,140
对  爱阿华州佩顿市 这是怎么回事?
Yes, sir. Peyton,Iowa, that's correct. What is this about?

1015
01:47:50,180 --> 01:47:52,880
你兄长阵亡了
Your brothers were killed in combat.

1016
01:47:59,860 --> 01:48:01,800
哪个?
Which ones?

1017
01:48:04,370 --> 01:48:06,660
全部
All of them.

1018
01:48:14,680 --> 01:48:17,300
真的?
On the level?

1019
01:48:18,650 --> 01:48:22,010
恐怕是真的
Yeah, I'm afraid so.

1020
01:48:23,280 --> 01:48:25,220
大概要一段时间才能接受
You might want to take some time with this.

1021
01:48:25,450 --> 01:48:28,720
要是你想到什么地方...
If there's someplace you want to go and...

1022
01:48:37,500 --> 01:48:40,330
是怎么回事? 瑞恩的兄弟去世了
-What's this all about?  -Ryan lost his brothers.

1023
01:48:40,540 --> 01:48:43,560
哪个? 全部
-Which one?  -All of them.

1024
01:48:51,880 --> 01:48:54,580
你们专程跑来告诉我?
You came all the way out here to tell me that?

1025
01:48:56,950 --> 01:49:00,180
你要回家
You're going home.

1026
01:49:00,390 --> 01:49:03,120
我们奉命带你回去
Our orders are to bring you back.

1027
01:49:06,630 --> 01:49:08,820
带我回去?
Bring me back?

1028
01:49:10,400 --> 01:49:15,200
下士  我并非想落井下石 但军令如山
Corporal,I don't mean to leave you more short-handed,but orders are orders.

1029
01:49:15,400 --> 01:49:18,030
想跟什么人联络吗?
Any communications about when you will be relieved?

1030
01:49:18,240 --> 01:49:21,170
我们也不知道南方的情况
We can't tell. We don't know what's happening south of us.

1031
01:49:21,410 --> 01:49:24,740
但我的命令不许我擅离职守
My orders don't include me abandoning my post.

1032
01:49:24,950 --> 01:49:27,570
一切以这道命令作准
I understand that, but this changes things.

1033
01:49:27,780 --> 01:49:30,050
我不认同
I don't see that it does, sir.

1034
01:49:31,690 --> 01:49:35,280
这是美军参谋长的命令
The Chief of Staff for the US Army says it does.

1035
01:49:35,490 --> 01:49:37,690
我们奉命死守这座桥
Our orders are to hold this bridge at all costs.

1036
01:49:37,890 --> 01:49:40,990
我方战机已经把麦德里特河的 所有桥梁炸断
Our planes in the 82nd have taken out every bridge across the Merderet,

1037
01:49:41,200 --> 01:49:43,990
除了瓦隆尼和这里两处
with the exception of two: one at Valognes and this one.

1038
01:49:44,200 --> 01:49:46,690
要是给德军拿下 我们就要退守
If the Germans take it, we'll have to displace.

1039
01:49:46,930 --> 01:49:51,840
部队的任务是一回事 但你要离开了
Private.It's one thing that your outfit wants to stay,but your party's over here.

1040
01:49:52,070 --> 01:49:53,940
援军到达前我不能离开
I can't leave before the reinforcements are here.

1041
01:49:54,140 --> 01:49:56,540
三分钟内收拾行装
You've got three minutes to get your gear.

1042
01:49:56,740 --> 01:50:00,480
那他们怎么办 混蛋
-What about them,there's barely...  -Hey,asshole!

1043
01:50:00,680 --> 01:50:04,580
我们两位队友已经为你送命
Two of our guys already died trying to find you.

1044
01:50:10,090 --> 01:50:13,030
真的? 不错
-Sir?  -That's right.

1045
01:50:22,600 --> 01:50:26,940
他们叫什么名字? 艾文韦德和艾德林卡帕佐
-What were their names?  -Irwin Wade and Adrian Caparzo.

1046
01:50:29,110 --> 01:50:30,630
韦德和谁?
Wade and?

1047
01:50:31,950 --> 01:50:33,680
卡帕佐
Caparzo.

1048
01:50:45,990 --> 01:50:48,330
没有理由要这样
It doesn't make any sense.

1049
01:50:50,470 --> 01:50:54,600
这样没道理 我何德何能  可以先走?
It doesn't make any sense, sir. Why do I deserve to go?

1050
01:50:54,800 --> 01:50:57,670
为何不是他们? 他们也同样努力
Why not any of these guys? They all fought just as hard as me.

1051
01:51:02,640 --> 01:51:05,740
你死后传讯员就要跟...
Is that what they're supposed to tell your mother

1052
01:51:05,950 --> 01:51:09,010
你母亲这样说?
when they send her another folded American flag?

1053
01:51:16,260 --> 01:51:19,520
跟她说你在这里找到我
Tell her that when you found me I was here,

1054
01:51:19,730 --> 01:51:22,490
我要跟军中其他手足一起
and I was with the only brothers that I have left,

1055
01:51:22,700 --> 01:51:26,780
我怎样也不会离弃他们
and that there was no way I was going to desert them.

1056
01:51:27,000 --> 01:51:32,170
她应该会明白 我不会离开这座桥
I think she'll understand that. There's no way I'm leaving this bridge.

1057
01:52:15,220 --> 01:52:17,280
现在怎么办?
What are your orders?

1058
01:52:19,090 --> 01:52:23,080
中士  我们进入了 一个奇异的国度
Sergeant, we have crossed some strange boundary here.

1059
01:52:23,320 --> 01:52:25,850
一切都异乎寻常
Our world has taken a turn for the surreal.

1060
01:52:26,090 --> 01:52:29,490
但问题始终要解决
Clearly, but the question still stands.

1061
01:52:29,700 --> 01:52:33,560
我不知道  你觉得怎样?
I don't know. What do you think?

1062
01:52:33,770 --> 01:52:36,260
你不会想知道
You don't want to know what I think.

1063
01:52:38,340 --> 01:52:40,500
不  我想知道
No, Mike, I do.

1064
01:52:43,670 --> 01:52:47,580
我其中一个想法是 如他所言  他何德何能?
Part of me thinks the kid's right. What's he done to deserve this?

1065
01:52:47,780 --> 01:52:51,780
他既然想留下来 我们就干脆回去
If he wants to stay here, fine. Let's leave him and go home.

1066
01:52:52,790 --> 01:52:54,650
不错
Yeah.

1067
01:52:54,860 --> 01:52:59,990
但我还有一个想法 要是我们也留下来
But another part of me thinks, "What if by some miracle we stay

1068
01:53:00,190 --> 01:53:02,960
会缔造什么奇迹呢?
and actually make it out of here?"

1069
01:53:03,160 --> 01:53:07,070
有天我们回想此事
Some day we might look back on this and decide that

1070
01:53:07,300 --> 01:53:11,750
也许会觉得在这场混帐战争中
saving Private Ryan was the one decent thing we pulled out of

1071
01:53:12,000 --> 01:53:16,770
拯救瑞恩是唯一的好事
this whole godawful, shitty mess.

1072
01:53:16,980 --> 01:53:23,780
这是我的想法 上尉  如你所言
That's what I was thinking, sir. Like you said, Captain.

1073
01:53:25,290 --> 01:53:30,440
我们会留下来 一起为团聚战斗
We do that, we all earn the right to go home.

1074
01:53:33,260 --> 01:53:35,390
兄弟
Oh, brother...

1075
01:53:38,030 --> 01:53:40,970
就只有这些
This is everything.

1076
01:53:41,170 --> 01:53:47,300
0.230机枪、17枚手榴弹 11个霍金斯地雷
You've got the.230 calibre machine guns, 17 grenades, 11 Hawkins mines.

1077
01:53:47,510 --> 01:53:50,700
你有两支火箭筒 但只能发射八次
You've got two bazookas, but they've only got eight rounds left.

1078
01:53:50,900 --> 01:53:53,040
还有各式小手枪
And assorted small arms.

1079
01:53:53,250 --> 01:53:56,480
本来有0.60迫击炮  但已损毁
We had a.60 mortar, but an arty round took it out.

1080
01:53:56,680 --> 01:53:59,300
敌军坦克压过来 吐口水攻击好了
Might as well be spit wads if they roll on us with tanks.

1081
01:53:59,510 --> 01:54:04,120
敌军当然会动用坦克 你意下如何?
Which they're sure to do. What are you thinking, sir?

1082
01:54:04,330 --> 01:54:07,730
我提议进行夹击
I'm thinking I'm going to whip around the flanks.

1083
01:54:12,060 --> 01:54:15,330
要把他们引到大街
Unless we can draw them up the main road between the buildings,

1084
01:54:15,540 --> 01:54:19,020
用瓦砾造一个瓶颈
where all the rubble makes a bit of a bottleneck

1085
01:54:19,260 --> 01:54:21,430
让坦克无用武之地? 可以的话
-Disable him?   -If we can.

1086
01:54:21,640 --> 01:54:25,270
造个六十吨的路障 然后展开夹击
Make a 60-tonne roadblock. Then we've got a fighting chance at her flanks.

1087
01:54:25,480 --> 01:54:27,600
好  分散他们  别让他们集结
Good. Split them up, don't let them mass.

1088
01:54:27,810 --> 01:54:30,680
然后逐一击破  再退回大桥
Hit them hard one-on-one, and fall back to the bridge.

1089
01:54:30,890 --> 01:54:35,220
下面放一台机枪 另一台置于高处
Machine gun on the move down here, number two up high to piss on them.

1090
01:54:35,420 --> 01:54:39,870
计划就是这样  杰克森
That would be the idea. Jackson!

1091
01:54:40,120 --> 01:54:42,430
可以的话  我想你去钟楼
If we can, I'd like to get you up in that bell tower.

1092
01:54:42,630 --> 01:54:45,660
知道 我会给你安排帮手
Yes, sir. I'll give you some company.

1093
01:54:45,900 --> 01:54:51,800
也好  还要0.30狙击枪 和一千发子弹
Some company couldn't hurt. A.30 with about a 1,000 rounds would be OK.

1094
01:54:52,030 --> 01:54:53,970
帕克  有份优差
Parker, job opportunity.

1095
01:54:54,210 --> 01:54:55,960
这主意不错
It's not the worst idea ever,

1096
01:54:56,170 --> 01:54:59,840
但胜负关键在于 把坦克弄到街上让我们夹击
but everything depends on getting the tank down the road for us to knock out.

1097
01:55:00,050 --> 01:55:03,380
你有什么主意?
How the hell do you plan on doing that?

1098
01:55:03,580 --> 01:55:06,240
他说得对  空降师的队友刚说
He's right. As our colleague from Airborne pointed out

1099
01:55:06,440 --> 01:55:08,710
我们有的是口水
what we've got is a bunch of spit wads.

1100
01:55:08,910 --> 01:55:12,760
但把坦克引来后  如何应付?
How do we stop the tank if we get it to commit?

1101
01:55:12,960 --> 01:55:14,430
先用兔子引它追赶
Give it a rabbit to chase.

1102
01:55:15,450 --> 01:55:18,120
接着攻击坦克的履带
We could hit the tank in the tracks.

1103
01:55:18,790 --> 01:55:20,120
对  但用什么攻击?
Yeah, but with what?

1104
01:55:22,600 --> 01:55:27,390
用粘附式炸弹 粘附式炸弹?
-We could try a sticky bomb.  -Sticky bomb, sir?

1105
01:55:27,600 --> 01:55:29,760
你编出来的吧?
Sir, are you making that up?

1106
01:55:29,970 --> 01:55:33,170
不  你可以去翻翻作战手册
No, it's in the field manual. Check it out, if you want to.

1107
01:55:33,380 --> 01:55:37,510
手册不知道在那里 你尽管讲解一下
We seem to be out of field manuals. Perhaps you could enlighten us.

1108
01:55:37,720 --> 01:55:40,950
有炸药吧?黄色炸药 还是B成分炸药?
You have some demolition, don't you? TNT or Composition B?

1109
01:55:41,160 --> 01:55:45,340
很多  桥那里的B炸药 足以把桥炸断两次
Plenty. I've got that bridge wired with enough Composition B to blow it twice.

1110
01:55:45,550 --> 01:55:47,040
那拿一点出来
You can spare some, then.

1111
01:55:47,820 --> 01:55:54,190
塞满军装袜子
You take a standard GI sock, cram it full with Composition B,

1112
01:55:54,390 --> 01:55:59,400
再加进导火线  表面涂满机油
and rig up a simple fuse. Then you coat the whole thing with axle grease.

1113
01:55:59,640 --> 01:56:03,000
炸弹扔出  就能粘附于目标物
That way, when you throw it, it should stick.

1114
01:56:03,200 --> 01:56:05,670
有粘力  所以叫粘附式炸弹
It's a bomb that sticks. It's a sticky bomb.

1115
01:56:05,900 --> 01:56:09,810
有更好的方法  尽管说出来
Come up with a better way to knock the tracks off a tank, I'm all ears.

1116
01:56:10,040 --> 01:56:13,530
这主意不错  大家要缴袜了
This is good. Now we have to surrender our socks!

1117
01:56:28,070 --> 01:56:29,660
拉上去
Haul away.

1118
01:56:43,340 --> 01:56:47,710
选择攻击范围 与钟楼组成交叉火力网
Select the field of fire. Crossfire with the one in the bell tower.

1119
01:56:47,910 --> 01:56:49,850
我负责12到9
I can cover 12 to 9 from here.

1120
01:56:54,120 --> 01:56:56,610
慢慢来 行了
Easy! I've got her!

1121
01:57:30,720 --> 01:57:32,660
这是地雷
Here are the mines.

1122
01:57:43,030 --> 01:57:45,810
要配置得当才行
For being the best we can do,

1123
01:57:46,010 --> 01:57:50,870
前头的机枪位置不太好
that forward machine gun is not in a terrible firing position.

1124
01:57:52,540 --> 01:57:54,980
应该放到这里
And this position right here...

1125
01:57:57,210 --> 01:57:59,240
这是最后防线
This is the Alamo.

1126
01:57:59,480 --> 01:58:02,820
要是退到这里 最后一个活人负责炸桥
They push us this far, the last man alive blows the bridge.

1127
01:58:03,020 --> 01:58:05,890
导火线能烧三十秒  告诉大家
We've only got a 30-second delay on the fuse, so tell everyone

1128
01:58:06,090 --> 01:58:10,720
点火后快逃  不然性命不保
that if you're last you'd better hurry or you'll not live long.

1129
01:58:11,600 --> 01:58:15,530
上尉?我有什么任务?
Captain? Where am I during all this?

1130
01:58:15,770 --> 01:58:20,100
留在我两英尺之内  不许有异议
Never more than two feet away from me. And that's not negotiable.

1131
01:58:21,140 --> 01:58:24,540
跟我去拿弹药
I'm going to get some ammo. Come on.

1132
01:58:26,680 --> 01:58:29,910
厄本  听着 是的
Hey, Upham, listen to me. Yes.

1133
01:58:30,110 --> 01:58:32,480
你在听吗? 是的
-Are you listening?  -Yes.

1134
01:58:32,680 --> 01:58:36,310
我们会不断东奔西跑
We're going to be displacing and falling back like crazy sons of bitches,

1135
01:58:36,520 --> 01:58:41,050
你要运送弹药  随传随到 不然我们就死定
so you've got to be Johnny-on-the-spot with the ammo,or we're dead.

1136
01:58:41,290 --> 01:58:42,690
你明白吗? 随传随到
-Do you understand?  -Johnny-on-the-spot.

1137
01:58:42,890 --> 01:58:46,760
你没事吧? 没事
-Yeah. Are you alright?  -Yeah.

1138
01:58:48,070 --> 01:58:51,190
我们从英国出发时 也会分发香烟
When we shipped out of England we got cigarettes

1139
01:58:51,400 --> 01:58:54,170
我却说“谢谢  我不抽烟”
and I said, "No, thank you. I don't smoke."

1140
01:58:58,780 --> 01:59:02,800
形势很凶险吧? 难以置信
-Quite a situation, huh?  -Unbelievable.

1141
01:59:03,050 --> 01:59:08,820
这差事混帐得不得了
Yeah. "Fucked-Up Beyond All Recognition", right?

1142
01:59:09,020 --> 01:59:11,490
不错
You've got that right.

1143
01:59:13,290 --> 01:59:16,620
“苦差” 对
-"FUBAR"!   -Alright!

1144
01:59:16,830 --> 01:59:18,060
很痛
Ouch.

1145
01:59:18,260 --> 01:59:22,360
这可不是玩的
Yeah, well... It's going to be a real show, huh?

1146
